# image/config.local — untracked, local-only build overrides.
#
# Copy this file to image/config.local (which is gitignored) and fill in your
# values. NEVER commit real credentials. build.sh appends config.local to the
# pi-gen config and uses the LI_WIFI_* values below to pre-provision Wi-Fi.
#
# Pre-provision a Wi-Fi connection so nodes join your network headless on first
# boot (handy when a node lives on the isolated lab switch with no other route
# in). The radio is unblocked by WPA_COUNTRY in image/config.
#LI_WIFI_SSID='YourNetwork'
#LI_WIFI_PSK='YourPassword'

# Set the WLAN regulatory domain for your region. image/config defaults this to
# the author's; override it here if you build (and bake Wi-Fi in) elsewhere.
# Two-letter ISO code (US, GB, DE, …). This appends after image/config, so the
# value here wins.
#WPA_COUNTRY='GB'

# You can also override any pi-gen config variable here, e.g. a stronger
# default password than the one baked into image/config:
#FIRST_USER_PASS='something-better'
